consistencychecker

Class ConsistencyChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • consistencychecker.ConsistencyChecker

  • public class ConsistencyChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an Ecore model consistency checker based on the mapping described by Calvanesi et al. Daniela Berardia, Diego Calvanese, Giuseppe De Giacomoa, Reasoning on UMLclass diagrams Artificial Intelligence, Volume 168, October 2005
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Cassio Santos, Christiano Braga
    See Also:
    http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.artint.2005.05.003

      • checkConsistency

        protected boolean checkConsistency()
                            throws ConsistencyCheckerGenericException
        Checks if the ontology associated with a model is consistent. Hermit returns a set of inconsistent classes when getUnsatisfiableClasses().getEntitiesMinusBottom() ; is called. If this set is empty our model is consistent and inconsistent otherwise.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the model is consistent and false otherwise
        Throws:
        ConsistencyCheckerGenericException
